We highlight the important role that LLMs play in improving KG construction, focusing on current trends, issues, and unanswered questions in this field.
We start by discussing link prediction, which is a way to generate new facts given an existing KG.
Next, we look at inductive link prediction, a method that predicts triples for unseen relationships. 
Our focus then shifts to a more recent method where triples is directly extracted from the parametric knowledge of an LLM.